article.headline: Oregon State 71, Arizona State 68
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Christian Polk scored 15 points and Jeff Pendergraph added 12 as Arizona State beat the University of Victoria 58-53 Tuesday night in an exhibition game. It marked the debut of new Sun Devils coach Herb Sendek, who was hired in April after 10 seasons at North Carolina State where he compiled a 191-132 record. Serge Angounou added 10 points for Arizona State, which led 26-23 at halftime and held on from there despite shooting only 39 percent from the field in the second half. Graeme Bollinger led Victoria with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Joshua Whyte had 13 points for the Vikes. Arizona State opens its season here Monday night against Northern Arizona.
